    public class ProjectExecutionOptions
extends java.lang.Object
    Project pre-and-post execution options.

    • Field Detail

      • rinputs

        public java.util.List<RData> rinputs
        List of DeployR-encoded R objects to be added to the workspace of the current R session prior to the execution. Pre-execution option.

      • csvrinputs

        public java.lang.String csvrinputs
        Comma-seperated list of primitive R object names and values, to be added to the workspace of the current R session prior to the execution. eg. csvrinputs=name,George,age,45 Pre-execution option.

      • preloadWorkspace

        public ProjectPreloadOptions preloadWorkspace
        Allows the loading of one or more named binary R objects from the repository into the workspace of the current R session prior to execution. Pre-execution option.

      • preloadDirectory

        public ProjectPreloadOptions preloadDirectory
        Allows the loading of one or more named files from the repository into the working directory of the current R session prior to execution. Pre-execution option.

      • preloadByDirectory

        public java.lang.String preloadByDirectory
        Allows the loading of all files found in one or more repository-managed directories into the working directory of the current R sesssion prior to execution. When loading the contents of more than one directory, use a comma-separated list of directory names. Pre-execution option.

      • adoptionOptions

        public ProjectAdoptionOptions adoptionOptions
        Allows the pre-loading of a pre-existing project workspace, project working directory, project history and/or project package dependencies into the current R session prior to an execution. Pre-execution option.

      • graphicsDevice

        public java.lang.String graphicsDevice
        Set R graphics device to use on execution: "png" or "svg". The default R graphics device is "png". On-execution option.

      • graphicsWidth

        public int graphicsWidth
        Set the width of the R graphics device on execution. On-execution option.

      • graphicsHeight

        public int graphicsHeight
        Set the height of the R graphics device on execution. On-execution option.

      • enableConsoleEvents

        public boolean enableConsoleEvents
        When enabled R console output events corresponding to the current execution will be sent on the event stream. On-execution option.

      • echooff

        public boolean echooff
        When enabled R commands are not echoed to the console output and will not appear in response markup or on the event stream. On-execution option.

      • consoleoff

        public boolean consoleoff
        When enabled all R console output is suppressed and will not appear in response markup. This control has no impact on console output on the event stream. On-execution option.

      • routputs

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> routputs
        List of workspace objects to be retrieved from the workspace of the current R session following the execution and returned as DeployR-encoded R objects. Post-execution option.

      • encodeDataFramePrimitiveAsVector

        public boolean encodeDataFramePrimitiveAsVector
        Workspace data.frame object encoding preference when retrieving R objects from the current R session following an execution. This option works in conjunction with the robjects property on this class. The default DeployR-encoding is to encode primatives inside data.frame objects as primitives, not as vectors. Post-execution option.

      • nan

        public java.lang.String nan
        Optional custom value to denote NAN values in DeployR-encoded objects in the response markup. Default is null. Post-execution option.

      • infinity

        public java.lang.String infinity
        Optional custom value to denote INFINITY values in DeployR-encoded objects in the response markup. Default is 0x7ff0000000000000L. Post-execution option.

      • storageOptions

        public ProjectStorageOptions storageOptions
        Repository storage options allow the storage of one-or-more workspace objects, the entire workspace and/or one-or-more working directory files from the current R session into the repository following the execution. Storage options are only available to AUTHENTICATED users on the call, ANONYMOUS users can not store data to the repository. Post-execution option.

      • tag

        public java.lang.String tag
        Optional tag to be associated with the execution that can be used later when viewing the execution history. Post-execution option.

      • phantom

        public boolean phantom
        When enabled meta-data about the execution is not recorded in the DeployR database and the execution does not appear in the RProject execution history.
